@node STATUS
@title "Status of the program"

The program "Check", the source code and the documentation are 
copyrighted. In short words : (c) @{" Stefan Diener " link AUTHOR}. It is allowed to
copy the program, while the following four points were accepted.

  1. It's not allowed to earn money by copying the program. (Only the
     disk the program is on may cost something.) If you've payed for
     copying this thing something went wrong. Please give me a little
     note.

  2. It is only allowed to copy the program together with the documen-
     tation and the source code. Just : "as it is" !

  3. It is not allowed to change anything in the program, the doc or the
     source.

  4. It is not allowed to put "Check" in any PD-series (or something
     similar) without a written permission by the author. There are two
     exceptions :
     * any collection from the S.A.U.G. e.V. (Germany) and
     * any collection from Fred Fish (disks or CD-ROM).
     It is welcome to put "Check" on any CD-ROM compilation. (Therefore
     you don't need any permission.)

"Check" was written using Maxon-Pascal 3.00 (MAXON Computer GmbH). 
(It has to be mentioned, I think ...)
@endnode

